;; cli-assist-full profile: clojure-mcp's structural editing + smart reader
;; brought back as FIRST-CLASS tools, for use alongside a CLI assistant
;; (e.g. Claude Code) where the agent drives and reviews later.
;;
;; First-class tools:
;;   - read_file                 (collapsed, structure-aware reader)
;;   - clojure_edit              (top-level form replace/insert)
;;   - clojure_edit_replace_sexp (targeted expression replacement)
;;   - paren_repair              (repair unbalanced parens)
;;   - clojure_eval              (REPL evaluation)
;;   - list_nrepl_ports          (discover running nREPL servers)
;;
;; Dirty-file handling (no Claude Code permission setup required):
;;   - :write-file-guard false   -> clojure-mcp never hard-blocks on staleness
;;                                  (safe: the editors above are content-addressed,
;;                                   they reparse the file fresh on every call)
;;   - :mcp-instructions steers ALL Clojure edits through the clojure tools so the
;;     host's native Edit never trips its own "modified since read" check on .clj.

{:mcp-instructions
 "Clojure tooling is available and PREFERRED for all Clojure source files (.clj, .cljs, .cljc, .bb, .edn).

- Read Clojure files with `read_file`: it returns a collapsed, structure-aware view (function signatures only by default, expandable by name/content pattern) that is far more token-efficient than a raw read.
- Edit Clojure files with `clojure_edit` (replace/insert a whole top-level form), `clojure_edit_replace_sexp` (replace a targeted expression), and `paren_repair` (fix unbalanced parentheses). These match by code structure rather than exact text, validate parentheses on the way in, and avoid the repeated string-match failures of generic editors.
- A persistent nREPL connection tool is available for evaluating and testing Clojure and ClojureScript code.

IMPORTANT — use the Clojure tools above for ALL edits to Clojure files, not the built-in Edit/Write tools. The Clojure tools rewrite files on disk; after one of them edits a file, the built-in Edit tool will see the file as changed and refuse with a \"file has been modified since read\" error until it re-reads. Routing every Clojure-file edit through the Clojure tools avoids this entirely. Keep using the built-in tools for non-Clojure files."

 :disable-tools
 [:grep
  :glob_files
  :bash
  :file_edit
  :file_write
  :scratch_pad
  :dispatch_agent
  :architect
  :code_critique
  :clojure_edit_agent
  :clojure_inspect_project]

 :disable-prompts
 ["create-update-project-summary"
  "plan-and-execute"
  "chat-session-summarize"
  "chat-session-resume"
  "ACT/add-dir"
  "ACT/scratch_pad_load"
  "ACT/scratch_pad_save_as"
  "save_new_prompt"
  "clojure_repl_system_prompt"]

 :disable-resources
 ["PROJECT_SUMMARY.md"
  "README.md"
  "CLAUDE.md"
  "LLM_CODE_STYLE.md"
  "Clojure Project Info"]

 :write-file-guard false}
